# Project kickoff to handover (typical 6-12 week engagement)

## Intent

From signed SOW to client-accepted final deliverable, with the freelancer running solo across discovery, build, and ship — no scope creep, weekly invoices paid on time, written handover + warranty period defined.

## Scope

From signed SOW to client-accepted final deliverable, with the freelancer running solo across discovery, build, and ship — no scope creep, weekly invoices paid on time, written handover + warranty period defined.

## Stages

### 1. Kickoff + stakeholder map

Set the working contract on day one.

Tasks:
- Run a 60-minute kickoff with all stakeholders
- Map decision-makers and reviewers
- Lock comms channels + cadence

Outputs:
- Kickoff notes
- Stakeholder map
- Comms cadence

Decision gate: Advance only when stakeholder map is signed off.

### 2. Discovery + requirements

Capture requirements properly, no vibes.

Tasks:
- Run elicitation interviews + workshops
- Document requirements with traceability
- Define acceptance criteria per requirement

Outputs:
- Requirements doc
- Traceability matrix
- Acceptance criteria

Decision gate: Advance only when client signs the requirements doc.

### 3. Architecture + risks

Pick the tech path and name the risks.

Tasks:
- Map quality attributes (perf, security, scale)
- Choose architecture and document decisions
- Surface top-5 risks with mitigations

Outputs:
- Architecture diagram
- ADRs
- Risk register

Decision gate: Advance only when risks have named mitigations.

### 4. Build sprints

Ship increments behind acceptance criteria.

Tasks:
- Run 1-week sprints with weekly demos
- Maintain CI/CD with health checks + logging
- Update the traceability matrix per sprint

Outputs:
- Sprint demos
- CI/CD pipeline
- Updated matrix

Decision gate: Advance only when every sprint ends with a working demo.

### 5. Scope-creep firewall

Block creep before it ruins the project.

Tasks:
- Log every change request
- Score impact on scope + timeline
- Either accept with a change order OR defer

Outputs:
- Change-request log
- Change-order docs
- Defer list

Decision gate: Advance only when no change is silently absorbed.

### 6. Weekly invoicing + cashflow

Money lands on time, every week.

Tasks:
- Send invoices on the agreed cadence
- Chase any overdue within 24h
- Reconcile against escrow / milestones

Outputs:
- Invoice log
- Chase log
- Reconciliation note

Decision gate: Advance only when no invoice is overdue by >7 days.

### 7. UAT + acceptance

Client validates against acceptance criteria.

Tasks:
- Run UAT sessions with the client
- Resolve UAT findings in priority order
- Get written acceptance

Outputs:
- UAT log
- Resolution PRs
- Acceptance email

Decision gate: Advance only with written client acceptance.

### 8. Handover pack

Leave behind a project that runs without you.

Tasks:
- Compile the handover package (docs, runbooks, credentials)
- Train the client team
- Define the warranty period + scope

Outputs:
- Handover package
- Training session log
- Warranty SOP

Decision gate: Advance only when client team can operate without you.

### 9. Testimonial + referral ask

Convert delivery into the next pipeline.

Tasks:
- Capture a written testimonial
- Ask for a referral to 2 similar buyers
- Close the engagement formally

Outputs:
- Testimonial captured
- Referral list
- Engagement closed

Decision gate: Cycle closes when testimonial + referrals are committed.

## Common pitfalls

- Skipping the decision-gate write-up to keep moving - closes the loop with vibes, not evidence.
- Treating each stages outputs as optional - every output is a gate input for the next stage.
- Letting one bad week stretch a fixed-cadence ritual into a quarterly one.

## Quality checklist

- Every stage has at least one referenced methodology that resolves under `knowledge/`.
- Every output is a real artefact, not a feeling.
- The final decision is a written commitment, not we will see.
